# PersAI session continuity

- Read in order before implementing: `AGENTS.md`, `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/API-BOUNDARY.md`, `docs/DATA-MODEL.md`, `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`, then any ADRs referenced by the **user's explicit task** only.
- **Active founder-opened program:** ADR-147 is the bounded Assistant Roles and Effective Skills orchestration program. Role belongs to each exact Assistant (including every Assistant in a B2B multi-assistant account); existing Skill/Scenario/Knowledge/runtime mechanics remain intact. S0 is accepted; S1 schema/expand, S2 role-only API/runtime/prompt, S3 user Role UX, S4 Admin Role constructor/MCP, S5a Release-B contract cutover, and S5b physical contract/drop are implemented, parent-audited CLEAN, and deployed. S5b release `a11c8b6b` passed isolated 189-migration proof, complete local/GitHub gates, migration-approved bot pin `05ccaed4`, Argo/exact-image/health/live DB acceptance, and refreshed user Settings Role visual. Release B `a225143e` remains the prior healthy bot pin `4c28dd52`; authenticated B2B acceptance proved three independently addressed Assistants and live `Маркетолог · Instagram-карусель` header indication. S6 remains open only for one authenticated Admin preview visual and a new-Agent-chat MCP catalog check: the current ordinary B2B Clerk session has no Admin entry and redirects `/admin/roles` to `/app`; existing Cursor chats retain their attached old MCP schema, so reload the server then open a new Agent chat. Implementation uses one sequential slice at a time. Cursor Grok 4.5 is the default subagent; GPT-5.4 is used only when stronger reasoning is necessary or Grok fails. Role UI is fully RU/EN, concise, premium, system-consistent; Admin Roles follows Admin Skills. ADR-146 is closed after S6 live acceptance. ADR-078, ADR-102, ADR-105–ADR-115, and the other closed numbered programs in `docs/ADR/` remain **closed archive**; do not reopen them or re-derive scope from them.
- Treat `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md` as the source of truth for the latest completed checkpoint and the user's next stated priority.
- Treat `docs/CHANGELOG.md` as the source of truth for what has actually landed.
- If ADR, handoff, changelog, and code disagree, stop and reconcile docs before code changes.
- One session = one bounded slice unless the user explicitly asks for broader work. New product/architecture waves require an explicit user priority and usually a **new ADR** before implementation.
- At session start, restate: task scope, purpose, likely affected files/modules, and what is out of scope.
- Start only from a clean git tree; if dirty, stop and report. Record baseline SHA in the handoff when the slice changes repo truth.
- Keep the architecture fully PersAI-native. Do not reintroduce OpenClaw runtime/deploy wiring, compatibility shims, filesystem-owned session state, or TODO scaffolding.
- Touch native OpenClaw only if historical analysis explicitly requires it and a PersAI-side change is insufficient.
- Before ending the session, update `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, update `docs/CHANGELOG.md` if repo truth changed, update or add an ADR only when long-term system truth changed, and state the next recommended step.
